J. LEROY SYKES v. STATE OF MARYLAND. [No. 23,

October Term, 1927.]

Decided January 11th, 1928.

The cause was argued before Bond, O. J., Pattison, Urner, Oeeutt, Digges, Parke, and Sloan, JJ.

Joshua Olayton, for the appellant. Thomas H. Robinson, Attorney General, Robert II. Archer, Assistant Attorney General, and Henry L. Constable, State’s Attorney for Cecil County, submitting on brief, for the State.

A

per curiam

opinion was delivered, dismissing the appeal.
